				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: This song is not useless<a name="8537"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jun 25 03 9:56 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>With the upgaded charm some dragons in WW can be charmed.
<br />

<br />
The bug:
<br />
A bug existed if you charmed a dragon then other dragons would assist your pet on its target.  Just like some old faction charm bugs that were discovered (thank you Fancy) ie charming the wood elf in rivervale PoD would assist your pet and charming trash in gfay scion would assist your pet.  Same deal here.  However SOE addressed this as soon as they found this out and fixed the factions.  Dragons now attack you if you a) attempt to charm a dragon and another is around or b) your pet dragon attacks something on CoV faction and another dragon is nearby.
<br />

<br />
The bugs been fixed! Now lets try! Not.
<br />
Dragons are dragons are dragons are dragons.  Dragons have an very high mr, they LOVE to break out of charm early.  Sometimes seconds after charm, usually 20 seconds.  Dragons summon! if you arent fast on your recharms things can hurt quickly.  Hope you have a healer close or you are fast with that ssbp.  Dragons have LOTS of hp.  You will be oom if you do not have some massive mana regen like MC3+FT4 (earring + boots of flowing slime to achieve easy).  A clear space with little adds.  You want some adds to help kil your pet of course but not to where it is unmanagable.  If you can work around all that then you can be rewarded with at most a 5*.
<br />

<br />
*Talismans drop occasionally of dragons in ww.  The number denotes the value of the talisman.  A 5 gives +5 to all stats and resists.  A 7 gives +7 to all stats and resits.  Esorpa should defintely be the target of kills as she is one of the lower level dragons and drops a 5.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
